data.title: COLLEGE FOOTBALL: SOUTH; Maryland Kick Ties Penn State
data.text:
Maryland ended a 24-game losing streak against Penn State when Dan DeArmas kicked his second field goal of the game, a 26-yarder with 58 seconds to play, to lift the Terrapins into a 13-13 tie with the Nittany Lions.

Maryland (3-6-1), which has not beaten Penn State since 1961, drove 57 yards in 11 plays to set up the tying field goal.

On their final possession, the Nittany Lions (6-2-1) moved the ball to the Maryland 48-yard line. The game ended when Tom Bill's pass into the end zone fell incomplete.

The Nittany Lions drove to inside the Maryland 20-yard line three times in the first half, scoring only on a 24-yard field goal by Tarasi with two seconds left in the half.

A Penn State running back, Blair Thomas, surpassed the 1,000-yard mark for the second time in his career. He gained 99 yards on 19 carries, giving him 1,051 yards this season. Arkansas 19, Baylor 10

FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) - An Arkansas freshman, Todd Wright, kicked four field goals, and a senior, James Rouse, had more than 100 yards rushing for the third successive week.
